Crafted with the water repellent diamond polyester fabric and sturdy hardware, FATMUG Foldable Duffel Bag 60L is a practical and multi-functional bag. This would be your go to companion for travelling as a weekender bag, spacious travel bag, emergency storage bag, overnight bag, camping Duffle, Airplane cabin luggage, carry-on luggage and much more. The foldable quality makes it extremely easy to carry to be your ideal secondary storage as and when needed.
Steps to Fold
Step 1
Lay your Fatmug Duffel Bag on a flat surface, with the front side facing down. Leave a slight opening on the main zipper and push out any excess air that may be inside the duffel bag.
Step 2
Fold excess fabric towards the middle of the bag. Make sure that both the shoulder and handle straps are put inside in the middle of the bag, and are not flapping outside.
Step 3
Fold the duffel bag from left to right, while ensuring all excess fabric and the handle stay inside the middle of the duffel bag.
Step 4
Begin to zip up the duffel into its own self-containing pouch. Please zip it up slowly, so you will not accidently snag any loose fabric. It is recommended to use one hand to zip the pouch and the other hand to push any loose fabric into the bag that may possibly snag on the zipper.

Steps to Fold
Step 1
Lay your Fatmug Duffel Bag on a flat surface, with the front side facing down. Leave a slight opening on the main zipper and push out any excess air that may be inside the duffel bag.
Step 2
Fold excess fabric towards the middle of the bag. Make sure that both the shoulder and handle straps are put inside in the middle of the bag, and are not flapping outside.
Step 3
Fold the duffel bag from left to right, while ensuring all excess fabric and the handle stay inside the middle of the duffel bag.
Step 4
Begin to zip up the duffel into its own self-containing pouch. Please zip it up slowly, so you will not accidently snag any loose fabric. It is recommended to use one hand to zip the pouch and the other hand to push any loose fabric into the bag that may possibly snag on the zipper.

YKK ZIPPERS
YKK -Those letters stand for "Yoshida Kogyo Kabushikikaisha" which, from Japanese, roughly translates to "Yoshida Company Limited." It's a zipper manufacturer named after Tadao Yoshida, who founded it in 1934. By one estimate, the company makes half the zippers on Earth, which is more than 7 billion zippers each year. YKK is known for manufacturing best zippers in the world.
